    "date": "2020-09-18T13:34:01Z",
    "text": "Preserving Employee Retirement Savings Act of 2020\n\nThis bill allows an employer that has a temporary substantial business hardship and, if not a tax-exempt or cooperative organization, does not have more that $41.5 million in gross receipts a tax credit for 20% of retirement contributions made to employee retirement accounts. The amount of such credit for any employer may not exceed $100,000 in any taxable year."
